## Summary

We have two files to maintain, schema.ts and index.ts
schema.ts contains the schema. If there are any changes, run this:

npx drizzle-kit generate
This generates the SQL file equivalent of the schema made in TSX
and compare the current database and SQL file

npx drizzle-kit migrate
This will now apply the changes to the database schema.

index.ts contains the actions to do in the database. To run it, use the command:

npx tsx src/index.ts

However, di ko sure if sa index.ts dapat ilagay lahat ng database functions kasi nabanggit ni tep na ilagay sa actions/auth-action.ts

## Long version, from docs

You can directly apply changes to your database using the drizzle-kit push command. This is a convenient method for quickly testing new schema designs or modifications in a local development environment, allowing for rapid iterations without the need to manage migration files:

npx drizzle-kit push

Alternatively, you can generate migrations using the drizzle-kit generate command and then apply them using the drizzle-kit migrate command:

Generate migrations:

npx drizzle-kit generate

Apply migrations:

npx drizzle-kit migrate

